data.description: Incl 06616012 & 14. Kenai River, 12'' custom log home,  three individual lots for 300 ft Kenai River frontage, with private, gated road and boat launch to the picnic area, fire pit, sandy beach, and elevated fishing platform. Oversized garage, heated with wood/coal stove or oil monitor heater, with a utility sink and upper level for storage and office with river view. No covenants. See Suppl. This is a unique property, owner built with attention to detail. The owner/builder was a general contractor and built several homes in the area. The lower walls were increased and extra insulated to be more energy efficient. After a chimney fire in 2015, the upper portion of the home has been completely upgraded and now has new kitchen, wood stove, heaters and a hot water heater. The home has a front deck and the entry door is solid wood, carved with an Alaskan scene (owls). The arctic entry enters to the kitchen or dining area, with wood accented kitchen cabinets, new kitchen appliances, a wood stove with slate backing or oil fired Monitor stove for heat. The living room has several large windows for view or glass doors to the back deck.  The half bath on the main level has a unique feature that also provides a river view. The upper level is the master suite, with vaulted ceilings, a paddle fan and space for an office, plus a full sized bathroom. The view is exceptional, day or night. The lower level has a  walk out basement with a nice family room, another bedroom and the laundry room/pantry. The detached garage is two story, with spruce siding and the interior is wired and insulated (urethane upstairs) and sheet rocked.  The wood shed over the 500 gallon oil tank is 12 X 16 ft, has a concrete footer, is wired and finished with stone and wood accents. The sauna is in the front lawn and has a barrel wood stove. The well is 80 feet deep and the septic system has a new leach field installed in 2010.
